<div class="col-12">
    <h3>Definitions</h3>
    <h5>Table Definition</h5>
    <div>
        Table generators were designed in an effort to mimic random tables often found in role-playing game source
        books. They consist of a series of tables that are populated with a number of options that determine how
        content is derived from them.
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                Properties
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h6 class="card-subtitle">In addition to the properties found in the <a asp-action="Index" asp-route-category="Definitions" asp-route-topic="BaseDefinition">Base Definition</a>, the following are specific to this definition type.</h6>
            <br />
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>&nbsp;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Output</th>
                        <td>
                            A string that formats the various values generated by the tables. More details can be found <a href="#output">below.</a>
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Tables</th>
                        <td>
                            The list of tables used to generate content.  See <a href="#tables">below</a> for more details.
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                <a id="output" />
                Output
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            The output is a string that contains variables created during the content generation process.
            Variables are included in the format <code>[TableName.ColumnName{?}]</code> or <code>[KeyId.ColumnName]</code> for loop tables where the optional <code>?</code> will cause the value to be an empty string if the variable does not exist.
            An asterisk can be used in the place of the Tablename in order to select the first instance of the ColumnName.<br />
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                <a id="tables" />
                Tables
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h6 class="card-subtitle">There are three types of tables, each is outlined in more detail below.</h6>
            <br />
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Type</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th><a href="#loopTable">Loop</a></th>
                        <td>Loops through each record and genertes content for each.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th><a href="#randomTable">Random</a></th>
                        <td>Selects a random row and generates content from it.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th><a href="#selectTable">Select</a></th>
                        <td>Selects a row based on a value and generates content from it.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>&nbsp;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>[Name]</th>
                        <td>The name of the table.</td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>TableType</th>
                        <td>
                            The type of table.<br />
                            <span class="font-weight-bold">Values:</span> Loop, Random, Select
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>SkipTable</th>
                        <td>
                            A calculation that determines if the table should be skipped.<br />
                            See the <a asp-action="Index" asp-route-category="Definitions" asp-route-topic="Expression">Expression</a> topic for more details.
                        </td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Repeat</th>
                        <td>
                            A number or calculation that determines the number of times to repeat processing the table.<br />
                            See the <a asp-action="Index" asp-route-category="Definitions" asp-route-topic="Expression">Expression</a> topic for more details.
                        </td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>EnumerateRepeat</th>
                        <td>
                            When repeating, if two of the same value are generated, added a number to the end.<br />
                            <span class="font-weight-bold">Default:</span> false
                            <span class="font-weight-bold">Example:</span> This, That x4, The Other x2
                        </td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>RepeatJoin</th>
                        <td>The string to put between values when repeating.</td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Table</th>
                        <td>
                            The formatted table to use in generation.<br />
                            <span class="font-weight-bold">Format:</span><br />
                            <pre>
ColumnHeader1 | ColumnHeader2
Row1Value1    | Row1Value2
Row2Value1    | Row2Value2
                            </pre>
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                <a id="loopTable" />
                Loop Table
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>&nbsp;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>KeyColumn</th>
                        <td>
                            Determines which column is used for the key id.<br />
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                <a id="randomTable" />
                Random Table
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>&nbsp;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>RollColumn</th>
                        <td>
                            Determines which column contains the dice roll.<br />
                            <span class="font-weight-bold">Default:</span> roll
                        </td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Modifier</th>
                        <td>
                            An expression that modifies the dice roll.<br />
                            See the <a asp-action="Index" asp-route-category="Definitions" asp-route-topic="Expression">Expression</a> topic for more details.
                        </td>
                        <td>&nbsp;</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                <a id="selectTable" />
                Select Table
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <table class="table">
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Property</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                        <th>&nbsp;</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>SelectColumn</th>
                        <td>
                            Determines which column to look for the SelectValue in.
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <th>SelectValue</th>
                        <td>
                            An expression that returns the value to look in the SelectColumn for.<br />
                            See the <a asp-action="Index" asp-route-category="Definitions" asp-route-topic="Expression">Expression</a> topic for more details.
                        </td>
                        <td><span class="bi-exclamation-circle-fill text-center" data-toggle="tooltip" data-html="true" data-placement="top" title="Required"></span></td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
    <br />
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h5 class="card-title">
                Example
            </h5>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="card-text">
                <pre>
                    <code>
<span class="font-weight-bold">Name:</span> Table Sample
<span class="font-weight-bold">Author:</span> Lance Boudreaux
<span class="font-weight-bold">Version:</span> "1.0"
<span class="font-weight-bold">Tags:</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">[</span>
	Sample
<span class="font-weight-bold">[</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">Parameters:</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
    Choice:
    <span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Value:</span> TableChoice
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Type:</span> List
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Options:</span>
        <span class="font-weight-bold">[</span>
            SampleTable1:One
            SampleTable2:Two
        <span class="font-weight-bold">]</span>
    <span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">OutputFormat:</span> Html
<span class="font-weight-bold">Output:</span>
'''	
&lt;Results&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
[SampleTable1.Value]&lt;br /&gt;
Bards: [Bard.Count]
Barbarians: [Barb.Count]
Guards: [Guard.Count]
'''
<span class="font-weight-bold">Tables:</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
    TableChoice:
    <span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
        <span class="font-weight-bold">TableType:</span> Select
        <span class="font-weight-bold">SelectColumn:</span> Choice
        <span class="font-weight-bold">SelectValue:</span> "=[Choice]"
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Table:</span>
            '''
            Choice       | Table
            SampleTable1 | =Table('SampleTable1')
            SampleTable2 | =Table('SampleTable2')
            '''
    <span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
    SampleTable1:
    <span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
        <span class="font-weight-bold">TableType:</span> Random
        <span class="font-weight-bold">SkipTable:</span> "=true"
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Table:</span>
            '''
            Roll | Value
            1    | Table1 Value1
            2    | Table1 Value2
            4    | Table1 Value3
            6    | Table1 Value4
            '''
    <span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
    SampleTable2:
    <span class="font-weight-bold">{</span>
        <span class="font-weight-bold">TableType:</span> Loop
        <span class="font-weight-bold">KeyColumn:</span> Type
        <span class="font-weight-bold">SkipTable:</span> "=true"
        <span class="font-weight-bold">Table:</span>
            '''
            Type    | Count
            Bard    | =Roll(1d6)
            Barb    | =Roll(1d4)
            Guard   | =Roll(1d20)
            '''
    <span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
<span class="font-weight-bold">}</span>
                    </code>
                </pre>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>